017package org.microbean.loader.spi;
018
019import java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType;
020import java.lang.reflect.Type;
021
022import java.util.function.Supplier;
023
024import org.microbean.development.annotation.OverridingEncouraged;
025
026import org.microbean.loader.api.Loader;
027
028import org.microbean.path.Path;
029
030import org.microbean.qualifier.Qualifiers;
031
032/**
033 * A skeletal {@link Provider} implementation.
034 *
035 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
036 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
037 *
038 * @see #lowerBound()
039 *
040 * @see Provider
041 */
042public abstract class AbstractProvider implements Provider {
043
044
045  /*
046   * Instance fields.
047   */
048
049
050  private final Type lowerBound;
051
052
053  /*
054   * Constructors.
055   */
056
057
058  /**
059   * Creates a new {@link AbstractProvider} with {@code null} as its
060   * {@linkplain #lowerBound() lower type bound}.
061   *
062   * @see #AbstractProvider(Type)
063   *
064   * @see #lowerBound()
065   */
066  protected AbstractProvider() {
067    this(null);
068  }
069
070  /**
071   * Creates a new {@link AbstractProvider}.
072   *
073   * @param lowerBound the {@linkplain #lowerBound() lower type bound}
074   * of this {@link AbstractProvider}; may be, and often is, {@code
075   * null}
076   *
077   * @see #lowerBound()
078   */
079  protected AbstractProvider(final Type lowerBound) {
080    super();
081    this.lowerBound = lowerBound;
082  }
083
084
085  /*
086   * Instance methods.
087   */
088
089
090  /**
091   * Returns a {@link Type} representing the <strong>lower bound of
092   * all possible {@linkplain Value values}</strong> {@linkplain
093   * #get(Loader, Path) supplied} by this {@link AbstractProvider}.
094   *
095   * @return the lower type bound of this {@link AbstractProvider}
096   * implementation, or {@code null} if its lower bound is the lowest
097   * possible bound
098   *
099   * @nullability This method may return {@code null}.
100   *
101   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
102   *
103   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
104   * threads.
105   */
106  @Override // Provider
107  public final Type lowerBound() {
108    return this.lowerBound;
109  }
110
111  /**
112   * Implements the {@link Provider#get(Loader, Path)} method to first
113   * call the {@link #find(Loader, Path)} method, and, if necessary,
114   * the {@link #path(Loader, Path)} method, and to then return a
115   * {@link Value} made up of the relevant return values.
116   *
117   * @param requestor the {@link Loader} seeking a {@link Value};
118   * must not be {@code null}
119   *
120   * @param absolutePath an {@linkplain Path#absolute() absolute
121   * <code>Path</code>} for which the supplied {@link Loader} is
122   * seeking a value; must not be {@code null}
123   *
124   * @return a {@link Value} more or less suitable for the combination
125   * of the supplied {@link Loader} and {@link Path}, or {@code
126   * null} if there is no such {@link Value} now <strong>and if there
127   * never will be such a {@link Value}</strong> for the supplied
128   * arguments
129   *
130   * @exception NullPointerException if either {@code requestor} or
131   * {@code absolutePath} is {@code null}
132   *
133   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code absolutePath}
134   * {@linkplain Path#absolute() is not absolute}, or if {@link
135   * Path#startsWith(Path)
136   * !absolutePath.startsWith(requestor.absolutePath())}, or if {@link
137   * Path#equals(Object)
138   * absolutePath.equals(requestor.absolutePath())}
139   *
140   * @nullability This method may return {@code null}.
141   *
142   * @idempotency This method is idempotent, but not necessarily
143   * deterministic.
144   *
145   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
146   * threads.
147   *
148   * @see Provider#get(Loader, Path)
149   *
150   * @see #find(Loader, Path)
151   *
152   * @see #path(Loader, Path)
153   */
154  @Override // Provider
155  public final Value<?> get(final Loader<?> requestor, final Path<? extends Type> absolutePath) {
156    final Supplier<?> s = this.find(requestor, absolutePath);
157    if (s != null) {
158      if (s instanceof Value<?> v) {
159        return v;
160      }
161      final Path<? extends Type> p = this.path(requestor, absolutePath);
162      if (p != null) {
163        return new Value<>(s, p);
164      }
165    }
166    return null;
167  }
168
169  /**
170   * Returns a {@link Supplier} suitable for the supplied {@link
171   * Loader} and {@link Path}, or {@code null} if there is no such
172   * {@link Supplier} now <strong>and if there never will be such a
173   * {@link Supplier}</strong> for the supplied arguments.
174   *
175   * <p>Overrides of this method must not call the {@link #get(Loader,
176   * Path)} method or undefined behavior (such as an infinite loop)
177   * may result.</p>
178   *
179   * @param requestor the {@link Loader} seeking a {@link Value} (as
180   * originally passed to the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method); must
181   * not be {@code null}
182   *
183   * @param absolutePath an {@linkplain Path#absolute() absolute
184   * <code>Path</code>} for which the supplied {@link Loader} is
185   * seeking a value (as originally passed to the {@link #get(Loader,
186   * Path)} method); must not be {@code null}
187   *
188   * @return a {@link Supplier} more or less suitable for the
189   * combination of the supplied {@link Loader} and {@link Path}, or
190   * {@code null} if there is no such {@link Supplier} now <strong>and
191   * if there never will be such a {@link Supplier}</strong> for the
192   * supplied arguments
193   *
194   * @exception NullPointerException if either {@code requestor} or
195   * {@code absolutePath} is {@code null}
196   *
197   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code absolutePath}
198   * {@linkplain Path#absolute() is not absolute}, or if {@link
199   * Path#startsWith(Path)
200   * !absolutePath.startsWith(requestor.absolutePath())}, or if {@link
201   * Path#equals(Object)
202   * absolutePath.equals(requestor.absolutePath())}
203   *
204   * @nullability Overrides of this method may return {@code null}, in
205   * which case the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method will return
206   * {@code null} as well.
207   *
208   * @idempotency Overrides of this method must be idempotent but are
209   * not assumed to be deterministic.
210   *
211   * @threadsafety Overrides of this method must be safe for
212   * concurrent use by multiple threads.
213   *
214   * @see #get(Loader, Path)
215   */
216  protected abstract Supplier<?> find(final Loader<?> requestor, final Path<? extends Type> absolutePath);
217
218  /**
219   * Returns a {@link Path} that will be {@linkplain
220   * Value#Value(Supplier, Path) used to build a <code>Value</code>}
221   * to be returned by the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method.
222   *
223   * <p>This method does not, and its overrides must not, call the
224   * {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method or undefined behavior (such as
225   * an infinite loop) may result.</p>
226   *
227   * <p>The default implementation of this method returns the supplied
228   * {@code absolutePath}.</p>
229   *
230   * <p>This method is called by the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method
231   * only when a call to the {@link #find(Loader, Path)} method
232   * returns a non-{@code null} value.</p>
233   *
234   * @param <T> the type of both the supplied and returned {@link
235   * Path}s
236   *
237   * @param requestor requestor the {@link Loader} seeking a {@link
238   * Value} (as originally passed to the {@link #get(Loader, Path)}
239   * method); must not be {@code null}
240   *
241   * @param absolutePath an {@linkplain Path#absolute() absolute
242   * <code>Path</code>} for which the supplied {@link Loader} is
243   * seeking a value (as originally passed to the {@link #get(Loader,
244   * Path)} method); must not be {@code null}
245   *
246   * @return a {@link Path} that will be {@linkplain
247   * Value#Value(Supplier, Path) used to build a <code>Value</code>}
248   * to be returned by the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method; if
249   * {@code null}, then the {@link #get(Loader, Path)} method will
250   * return {@code null} as well
251   *
252   * @exception NullPointerException if either {@code requestor} or
253   * {@code absolutePath} is {@code null}
254   *
255   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code absolutePath}
256   * {@linkplain Path#absolute() is not absolute}, or if {@link
257   * Path#startsWith(Path)
258   * !absolutePath.startsWith(requestor.absolutePath())}, or if {@link
259   * Path#equals(Object)
260   * absolutePath.equals(requestor.absolutePath())}
261   *
262   * @nullability This method does not, but its overrides may, return
263   * {@code null}.
264   *
265   * @idempotency This method is, and its overrides must be,
266   * idempotent and deterministic.
267   *
268   * @threadsafety This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for
269   * concurrent use by multiple threads.
270   *
271   * @see #get(Loader, Path)
272   */
273  @OverridingEncouraged
274  protected <T extends Type> Path<T> path(final Loader<?> requestor, final Path<T> absolutePath) {
275    return absolutePath;
276  }
277
278}
